<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by SensoO:
[I]Ok KnightWolf,

You're missing the point of this type of rpg. You seem to want fewer options and the ability to from point A to point B without any bumps in the road. Diablo seems just right for you (if you want to run around with potions all day). In this game, there is an emphasis on leveling your character and figuring out all of the special goodies Larian added for our benefit.

Run out of potions? Use alchemy. No alchemy? Eat some meat. No meat? Kill a bunnie...

Not powerful enough? Hunt anything you can kill. I was level 8 before I started the 2nd level of the catacombs. How? I went on an orc killing spree outside the town once I was level 3. This game gives you so many choices and options. It's not made for someone who wants to rely on potions all day. There are many choices one has to make in this game and if you take the time to understand it, the game won't be too difficult for you.

And about not remembering to save your game... I swear, can you not take responsibility for your own actions? That's not Larian's fault. This game is a thinkers game in many aspects. If you can't handle it, play tetris or something.
[/I][/QUOTE]

