 with situations, but only a small percentage of the options available. I love the fact that there are so many ways of dealing around situations. I get board when I master one tactic and I'm always looking for new ones. And believe me I am not a great roleplayer by any means.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">paddyjack</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Myself I found that game amazing for the possibilities you can do. I'm still early in the game, at level 15. I think that Knightwolf's opinion was biased because he went to the Abbey so fast. Myself I looked at the map and it was written "very dangerous" for the Abbey, so I decided to postpone my goinf there. This is what you should do. Of course, some games like Diablo send you to one dungeon after another, so you face monsters balanced to fit your skill level. But the point of DD is to explore where your skill level allow you to (just like many other RPG btw).<P>As for potions, well if you explore where you are skilled enough to do so, then you hardly need these potions. I have something like 20 of healing and mana in my inventory right now, and I do not have alchemy skill.<P>But if you still do not like the game, well you are entitled to your opinion!<P>Paddyjack<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Drathen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I love the game so far, I'm level 17/18 (I forget which), kicking around Verdistis.  My only complaint is that magic potions are so rare.  When I *have* mana, I can really kick ass as my mage, but once the teleporter stones are gone, its hard to replenish mana (with a max mana of 350, it takes a ton of potions just to be able to get your mana up to half).<P>Herbs being more common would have been nice...<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.